One of the classical directions of anisotropy studies is the search for large-scale anisotropy of UHECRs. The Pierre Auger collaboration presented results of two Rayleigh analyses, one in the right ascension and one in the azimuth angle distributions, of the arrival directions of events with energy above 4 EeV and zenith angle up to 80∘\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
