The scientific equipment installed onboard the Lomonosov satellite includes the number of instruments intended for solving scientific problems mentioned above:
An optical wide aperture telescope TUS for imaging of the UHECR tracks in the atmosphere;
A set of instruments for GRB study including gamma-ray monitor BDRG, optical wide-field cameras SHOK, and UFFO instruments consisting of UV and X-ray telescopes;
A set of instruments studying the energetic particle fluxes in the near-Earth space including magnetometer, high-energy electron detector ELFIN-L and charge and neutral particle monitor DEPRON; and
The IMISS-1 instrument for recording and analysis of accelerations in orbital flight.

